Nicolas   Mirzayantz  Group President of Fragrances, International Flavors & Fragrances Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 2 different industries.See Board Relationships54$2,260,466As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Nicolas Mirzayantz has been the Group President of Fragrances at International Flavors & Fragrances Inc. since January 2007. In this role, Mr. Mirzayantz is responsible for global strategy, commercial and creative execution, people development and profit and loss in the Fragrances Business Unit. Mr. Mirzayantz serves as President of IFF’s prestigious unit of natural products, Laboratoire Monique Rémy in Grasse, France. He has extensive experience in the creation ... and sales of fine fragrances. Mr. Mirzayantz served as Secretary of Research Institute for Fragrance Materials, Inc. He served as Senior Vice President of Fine Fragrance and Beauty Care of International Flavors & Fragrances Inc. since October 2004 until February 2005 and was its Member Temporary Office of the CEO from October 1, 2009 to February 2010. He was responsible for IFF’s Global Fine Fragrances Group, including Beauty Care as well as the general management of the business development and operations activities in North America, including flavors and functional fragrances. Additionally, he oversaw the integration and development of IFF’s Creative Centers in New York and Paris. He served as a Vice President of Global Business Development for Fine Fragrance and Toiletries at International Flavors & Fragrances Inc., since December 2002 until September 2004 and served as its Regional Manager of North American Region since April 2005. Mr. Mirzayantz served as Vice President, Global Business Development of Fine Fragrances and Toiletries since January 2001, Fragrances General Manager of IFF France from January 1999 to January 2001; and also served as Vice President of Commercial and Creative Director of IFF France. Mr. Mirzayantz joined IFF’s Creative Center in Paris in 1988 and has held increasingly responsible positions during his more than 20-year career with the company. He oversaw IFF's Creative Centers in New York and Paris, as well as its prestigious unit of natural products, Laboratoire Monique Rémy in Grasse, France. At IFF, he was in charge of integrating the New York and Paris Creative Centers to reflect its global strategy in its fine fragrance business. He joined IFF France in 1988 as a Member of the sales team and held increasingly senior positions as part of IFF's fine fragrance account team. Prior to his appointment as Commercial and Creative Director in France, he spent four years as Vice President, Global Account Manager for Estée Lauder, based in New York. Prior to IFF, he served as Deputy Trade Commissioner at the French Embassy in Nicaragua in 1986 and 1987. He serves as Vice Chairman of the Board of Directors and Director at Research Institute for Fragrance Materials, Inc. He is Vice Chair, Industry Advisory Board for the Fashion Institute of Technology (FIT) Master’s Program. He serves on the board of the International Fragrance Association (IFRA). Mr. Mirzayantz holds a baccalauréat degree in Economics and a Master of Economics degree from the University of Paris II ASSAS. He also completed the International Executive Program at INSEAD in Fontainebleau in 1998.Read Full Background




